      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="947B62MJ" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-947B62MJ-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-947B62MJ-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-947B62MJ-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">────<hi rend="underline">to Mrs. Houghton, on her praising her husband</hi> This is so delicate a compliment, that we dare say our Readers will be pleased with it: the rather too, as delicacy is not always to be expected from the pen of this witty, but licentious, Writer.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-947B62MJ-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-947B62MJ-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-947B62MJ-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-947B62MJ-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-947B62MJ-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-947B62MJ-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-947B62MJ-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">Y</hi>OU always are making a God of your spouse,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-947B62MJ-line-2"> But this neither reason nor conscience allows;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-947B62MJ-line-3"> Perhaps you adore him, because he adores you.</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-947B62MJ-line-4"> Your argument's weak, and so you will find,</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-947B62MJ-line-5"> For you, by this rule, must adore all mankind.947B62MJ   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
